      "instruction": "<p>Combine <strong>half</strong> the<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>white miso paste</strong> with the<strong> honey </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>miso honey glaze</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>remaining white miso paste </strong>with the<strong> rice vinegar </strong>and<strong> half </strong>the <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) – this is your <strong>miso dressing</strong></p><p>Wash then cut the <strong>pak choi </strong>into halves, lengthways, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Preheat the grill to medium-high</p>",
